HEADWORD: Titillate
<hw>Tit"il*late</hw> <pr>(t⟦icr⟧t"⟦icr⟧l*l⟦amac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v. t. &
i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Titillated</conjf>
<pr>(t⟦icr⟧t"⟦icr⟧l*l⟦amac⟧`t⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Titillating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>titillatus</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>titillare</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To tickle; <as>as,
to <ex>titillate</ex> the nose with a feather</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pungent grains of <qex>titillating</qex> dust.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To arouse an agreeable sensation in; <as>as, to
<ex>titillate</ex> one's imagination; to <ex>titillate</ex> one's
audience; to <ex>titillate</ex> the senses</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>titillation</ent>⟦br⟧
